\#\#\# Top Answer: Delay defining `Hash::operator()` until after defining `Node` and declare `Node` before `Hash`. You can have a reference to an incomplete type as long as you don't do anything with it.

```
class Node;

class Hash{
    public:
        size_t operator()(const Node &node) const;
};

class Node{
    public:
        int data;
        unordered_set<Node, Hash> links;
};

inline size_t Hash::operator()(const Node &node) const{
    return node.data;
}

```

